{
  "texts": [
    "Algorithm 1 is the proposed method, which permits edge repetition for vertices in meta-structures with multiple bifurcations.",
    "1 u 2 m 1 u 3 m 1 u 4 m (a) Original HG 1 u 1 m 1 u 2 m 1 u 3 m We use l to denote the number of vertical layers (i.e., levels) of the meta-structure and traverse each layer of the meta-structure.",
    "For layers containing multiple vertex types, where bifurcation appear, we initialize a Map M and a set B on lines 3-4.",
    "We collect the set of all vertices where the bifurcation begins, denoted as A (e.g., all vertices of type M), and then decompose this meta-structure into a set P of meta-paths on lines 5-6.",
    "We traverse every vertex u of the set A, finding the meta-path instances in P using the depth first search (DFS)."
  ]
}